		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />A few years ago I made 7-Zip my default archive program, and considering that it's free, while WinRar and WinZip are not, I'd say that was a good choice. It doesn't compress to RAR, but it does compress to both ZIP and 7Z, and decompresses anything I've tried so far.

		

